{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-03715/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-03715"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:37:15"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking, pan, tilt, crane"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man leads a woman into his bedroom."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03715/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-03715","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03715/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-03715"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03715/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03715/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03715/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03715/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03715/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03715/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03715/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03715/canvas/1/63655532-7e8d-4ae7-8490-d37d4687b5b5","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T17:30:22.446Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This dress with its lace designs was designed with Reynolds’s wedding gown for the Belgian princess in mind. According to costume designer Mark Bridges, this trait is part of the Woodcock sensibility that the production developed (Harris, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW188147706 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.vulture.com/2018/01/the-story-behind-phantom-threads-majestic-couture-dresses.html\"><u>The Story</u></a>”). The contrast between the Princess’s white dress and Alma’s black dress is quite telling, too. Alma represents Reynolds’s dark temptations, and her own willingness to go dark keeps him in check. This contrast goes all the way back to the opening title card, of course.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03715/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:922.5302826379542,354.5895020188426,374.69717362045765,534.9125168236877"}}}]}]}]}